    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I hope for another seven years we may as last carry on our correspondence by
                    means of <persName ref="pe0015">my worthy neighbour</persName>, whom we
                    re-elected last week. I hope soon to hear from <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> who will now have ample time to
                    pursue his studies; &amp; I dare say will do himself credit. a few of the coins
                    &amp;c will be welcome but that at y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> full leisure.
                    I shall be in <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName> from Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> to Jan. 20<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> ready to receive y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                    command in the interim inclose as usual.</p>
                <p>Somebody called at <persName ref="pe0026">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Whites</persName> to say he c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> inform me of
                    something relating to <placeName ref="pl0750">Fair isles</placeName>; &amp; that
                    He w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> write to me; but I never yet have heard from
                    him. He was a N. Briton.</p>
                <p>I really think <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0127">Slezers
                        plates</title>
                    </bibl> not faithful enough to merit a new edition.</p>
                <p>All I can do to serve the publisher of <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0081">the history of Murray</title>
                    </bibl> shall be done. They are best judge
                    of the expence they can go to about the plates. A map is really necessary. Could
                    they not extract it from <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0126">Dorrets
                            great map</title>
                    </bibl> &amp; correct it from their own acquaintance
                    with the County. I have corrected my error about the Scottish Kings at
                        <placeName ref="pl0146">Kinloss</placeName>; so hope they will take no
                    notice of it.</p>
                <p>I have not seen <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0213">the acc<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> of roman antiquities</title>
                    </bibl> at
                        <placeName ref="pl0127">Banchorie</placeName>, <sic>so be you w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> cut out the paragraph.</sic> also the 2
                    letters from <placeName ref="pl0110">Athol</placeName>. the rest I can wait
                    for.</p>
                <p>Weather very fine for the last 3 weeks. I am sorry to hear <persName ref="pe0132">Sir L. Dundas</persName> meets with any disturbance. <placeName ref="pl0731">S. Britain</placeName> in general is very quiet.</p>
                <p>I inclose an order for 4 appendices. If <persName ref="pe0180">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Balfour</persName> has any I wish one apiece
                    may be sent to <persName ref="pe0158">the Rev<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Macintyre</persName> of <placeName ref="pl0213">Glenorchie</placeName>. to <persName ref="pe0310">the Rev<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Sutherland</persName>
                    <placeName ref="pl0165">Dornoch</placeName>. <persName ref="pe0247">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Professor W. Oglevie</persName>
                    <placeName ref="pl0129">old aberdeen</placeName>, &amp; <persName ref="pe0114">Doctor Saunders</persName>
                    <placeName ref="pl0136">Banff</placeName>. <persName ref="pe0180">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Balfour</persName> may replace them by virtue
                    of my order.</p>
                <p>Is the rest of <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0109">Perth
                        Gabions</title>
                    </bibl> published.</p>
                <closer>I am <lb/>Dear Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>

                <dateline>
                    <placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Oct<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 23<hi rend="superscript">d.</hi> 1774.</dateline>

                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <bibl type="authorial">
                            <title ref="bi0530">The extracts from the advocates
                                library</title>
                        </bibl> contain so little as not to merit the <add place="above">trouble</add>
                        <unclear reason="illegible">tro</unclear> of transcribing. but my
                        obligations to <add place="above">you</add>
                        <unclear reason="illegible">y</unclear> are the same.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
